# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveDevice
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#MedicalDevice> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A medical device whose operation depends on a source of energy other than that generated by the human body or gravity." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Active Device" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveImplant
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveImplant> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveImplant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveDevice> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveImplant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableDevice> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveImplant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An implantable device that also requires a source of energy to operate. Combines properties of both ActiveDevice and ImplantableDevice." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveImplant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Active Implant" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassA
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassA> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassA> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#IVDRClass> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassA> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Lowest IVDR risk class. Low individual and public health risk." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassA> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "IVDR Class A" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassB
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassB> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassB> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#IVDRClass> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassB> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Low-medium IVDR risk class." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassB> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "IVDR Class B" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassC
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#IVDRClass> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Medium-high IVDR risk class. Devices used for detection of serious conditions." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "IVDR Class C" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassD
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassD> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassD> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#IVDRClass> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassD> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Highest IVDR risk class. Devices for detection of life-threatening conditions or blood screening." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassD> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "IVDR Class D" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassI
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassI> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassI> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#MDRClass> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassI> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Lowest MDR risk class. Devices pose minimal risk to patients and users." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassI> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Class I" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIII
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#MDRClass> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Highest MDR risk class. Devices that support or sustain life, implantable or cause serious risks." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Class III" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIIa
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#MDRClass> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Medium-low MDR risk class. Devices intended for short-term use or moderate risk." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Class IIa" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIIb
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIIb> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIIb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#MDRClass> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIIb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Medium-high MDR risk class. Devices with higher potential hazard to patients." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ClassIIb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Class IIb" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#CorrectiveAction
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#CorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#CorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#MedicalEntity> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#CorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An action taken by a manufacturer to reduce risk associated with a medical device already placed on the market (FSCA)." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#CorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Field Safety Corrective Action" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#IVDRClass
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#IVDRClass> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#IVDRClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#RegulatoryClass> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#IVDRClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk classification under the In Vitro Diagnostic Regulation (EU 2017/746). Includes Class A, B, C, and D." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#IVDRClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "IVDR Risk Class" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableActiveDevice
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#ActiveImplant> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A fully implantable active device with integrated energy source, such as a ventricular assist device." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Implantable Active Device" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableDevice
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#MedicalDevice> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A device intended to be totally or partially introduced into the human body and to remain after the procedure." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#ImplantableDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Implantable Device" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#InSituCorrection
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#InSituCorrection> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#InSituCorrection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#CorrectiveAction> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#InSituCorrection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A FSCA where the device is corrected on-site without removal." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#InSituCorrection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "In Situ Correction" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#InVitroDiagnosticDevice
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#MedicalDevice> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A device intended to examine specimens derived from the human body, as defined in IVDR EU 2017/746." .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "In Vitro Diagnostic Device" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/eudamed#Incident
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#MedicalEntity> .
<http://www.example.org/eudamed#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid1 .
_:genid1 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#minCardinality> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger> .
_:genid1 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://www.example.org/eudamed#isReportedFor> .
